  <static seed="1301" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions141.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{-x^{2}-7xt-6t^{2}}{x^{2}-36t^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{x+t}{x-6t}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms.</p>
<p>If a polynomial is not in order, we order it by the variable<rsq/>s degrees.</p>
<p>If the leading coefficient is negative, we factor out <m>-1</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{-x^{2}-7xt-6t^{2}}{x^{2}-36t^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{-\left(x^{2}+7xt+6t^{2}\right)}}{{x^{2}-36t^{2}}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-\left(x+t\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+6t\right)}}{{\left(x+6t\right)\mathopen{}\left(x-6t\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{x+t}{x-6t}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
